Today we completed roll out of a new home timeline ranking model to make posts you see more relevant.

- 10x user and post embedding parameters
- 5x faster realtime training parameter updates
- 3x training compute

Follow here for updates as we continue to scale core recommendation systems in pursuit of unregretted user seconds.

PSA for X API V2 users:
Consider being an early adopter of the api route segment changes to reflect rebranding of tweets to posts. 
i.e try replacing endpoint paths having "tweet"/"tweets" with "post"/"posts"

So for example:
GET /2/tweets -> GET /2/posts
POST /2/tweets -> POST /2/posts
‚Ä¶ and so on

let me know how it goes. thanks!

result.text:
Announcing new X API V2 endpoints to support more programmatic access to X features as part of the referenced self-serve changes:

1. GET /2/users/personalized_trends: allows authenticated premium users to get personalized trends (similar to ones shown on the Explore page)

2. GET /2/users/reposts_of_me: allows fetching of all reposts (f.k.a retweets) of the requesting user

3. GET /2/communities/search: allows searching for eligible communities via a keyword

4. GET /2/communities/:id: allows fetching metadata of a community by id

For more information, visit: https://t.co/rOX3rDsXI4
